  "texts": [
    "The Hypothesis Generator uses a multi-step approach to generate questions that are both interesting and easy to answer for the given database.",
    "It is composed of two elements.",
    "A high-level generator HL-G that uses a prompt (Appendix E.2) to generate overarching questions h i.",
    "The high-level generator uses a short description of the database (short(D info)) that we shorten to prevent constraining the model's response with database details, enabling more exploratory questions within the domain: HL-G(short(D info)) → h 0,.",
    ", h n A low-level generator LL-G splits the high-level question h i into subquestions s ij."
  ],
